decisions:
  - Stored `language` alongside the existing preferences schema in localStorage, defaulting to `zh`.
  - Implemented `LanguageProvider` with a simple in-house `t(key, params)` lookup instead of adding a third-party i18n library.
  - Kept flashcard fronts language-selective while making flashcard backs explicitly bilingual through new `back.*Zh` and `back.*En` fields.
  - Localized quick-reference body copy through bilingual card-back content plus bilingual checklist item objects.
evidence:
  - `npm test -- --run` -> 7 test files passed, 19 tests passed
open_risks:
  - none
summary: Added a persistent Chinese/English language toggle to the app shell, routed all page/component UI copy through a new language provider and translations map, localized lesson titles/summaries and quick-reference content, expanded flashcard back data to carry both languages while preserving the existing study flow, updated tests for the new provider requirements, and committed the implementation at `02c604da337c98dd8f4fc710df80923d34954c66`.
